ctftime.description: CSAW CTF is a entry-level CTF, designed for undergraduate students who are trying to break into security. Our judges are world-renowned experts in the security field, who are dedicated to making sure that our challenges are designed to test these skills.

ctftime.description: CTF, the centerpiece of CSAW, celebrates the tenth anniversary of its illustrious history of inspiring undergraduates to learn more about computer security. We are pleased to announce that the HITCON CTF “Attack & Defense” competition is about to start.

Time for qualification is Oct 17 10:00 AM ~ Oct 18 10:00 PM (GMT+8, 36 hours)
Top 10 teams will be invited  to HITCON CTF Final in Dec 5-6 (Onsite Attack & Defense in Taipei)       

1. Qualification is online jeopardy including reversing, pwnable, crypto, forensic, web, misc...
2. We will "partially" support top 10 teams for their flight and accommodation.
3. Awards in final:  1st place: $10,000 USD, 2nd place: $5,000 USD, 3rd place: $2,000 USD. Special award fo Top 1 Taiwan team: $1,000 USD
4. Online registration will open at Oct 4 3:00 PM. Please keep following our official website: http://ctf.hitcon.org

Quals: Online Jeopardy, Oct 17-18, 2015
Final: Attack & Defense, Dec 5-6, 2015 (4 players / team)

Currently 2015 HITCON CTF Qualifying Contests:
The champions of the following contests will pre-qualify directly for the final in December and do not need to participate in the preliminary in 17th October.
1. TrendMicro CTF Japan
2. AIS3 Challenges
3. CTCTF 2015

ctftime.description:
Trend Micro CTF Asia Pacific & Japan 2015 is an event hosted by Trend Micro, a global leader in security software and solutions with the vision ‘a world safe for exchanging digital information’.

Trend Micro CTF Asia Pacific & Japan 2015 combines online qualifier and on-site final. Top ten teams from the qualifier will automatically qualify for the final, hosted in Tokyo in November 2015.

Challenges include not only orthodox categories such as ‘binary analysis’ and ‘packet analysis’, but also ‘targeted attacks’, ‘virtualisation', etc., to reflect the current and future business IT environments.

Requirement
- Resident in Asia Pacific and Japan countries and regions (*see official website for more details)
- Adults aged over 20
- Please note that participants who are from outside Asia Pacific & Japan countries and regions and finished among top ten will not be eligible for participating in the final.

Schedule
Duration: 24hrs
Program: Jeopardy-style
Challenge categories include, in addition to ‘binary’ and ‘packet’, ‘targeted attack’, ‘IoT’, and ‘ICS/SCADA’ planned - 30 challenge, with five in six different categories planned
Language:English (with Japanese support)

ctftime.description: HITCON CTF already has a history of 9 years. From this year, it will be online and opened to all participants around the world. ctftime.description:
2016, Let’s get fun again with HITCON's  "Attack & Defense"!

Time for qualification is Oct 8 10:00 AM ~ Oct 10 10:00 AM (GMT+8, 48 hours)
Top 10 teams will be invited to HITCON CTF Final in Dec 2-3 (Onsite Attack & Defense in Taipei)
